## How to use

### Accessible placeholder

Provide `accessiblePlaceholder: true` and a `label` to create an accessible placeholder for the input.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/search/examples/search-placeholder/index.njk"})
}}

### Use appropriately sized inputs

A [width constraint](/components/input#width-constrained) class can be used to make the width of input smaller. If the search context is known, for instance a sequence of characters of a known size, the width constraint can help users.

### Variants

#### Character check

The character check counter is displayed when the `charcheck`, `charCountOverLimitSingular`, `charCountOverLimitPlural`, `charCountPlural` and `charCountSingular` parameters are defined.

The button is disabled unless the input value matches the value supplied to the `charcheck` param.

